setSElementId

void setSElementId(SElementId value)
Sets the identifier of this node SRelation object. Note, that an identifier must be unique inside the graph which contains the node. The id can also be used as an uri and therefore has to respect some syntax restrictions. In general the identifier will be set by the graph when adding the SRelation object to the graph, therefore in most cases it would be better to take the identifier given by the graph and not to change it. To have an influence on the id set the name of the SRelation object by calling setSName().

Specified by:
setSElementId in interface SIdentifiableElement
Parameters:
value - the new value of the 'SElement Id' reference.
